{"type":"message","id":"723bf591","parentId":"d73afd22","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:23:51.900Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The process tool requires a sessionId for exec actions. Looking at the tool description more carefully, it seems like I need to first create a session somehow. But the actions listed are: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill - there's no \"create\" or \"exec\" action to start a new session.\n\nWait, looking at the skill documentation again, it mentions using native tools directly if the plugin is installed. The native tools would be: tavily_search, tavily_extract, tavily_crawl, tavily_map, tavily_research.\n\nBut these aren't showing up in my available tools. This suggests the plugin might not be properly installed or configured.\n\nLet me check if there's a configuration for the tavily plugin in the OpenClaw config.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c374a754327145d997d4957c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/config.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773505428169}}
