{"type":"message","id":"d46d97ea","parentId":"b80fbbca","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:23:59.774Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The process tool requires a sessionId but I don't have a way to create one with the available actions. Let me look at the process tool description again more carefully.\n\nLooking at the process tool parameters:\n- action: Process action (required)\n- sessionId: Session id for actions other than list (optional based on description)\n- data, eof, hex, keys, limit, literal, offset, text, timeout, bracketed: various optional parameters\n\nThe description says \"Manage running exec sessions: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill.\"\n\nSo \"exec\" isn't even a valid action. The actions are: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill.\n\nThis means I can't directly execute commands with the process tool. I need to use a different approach.\n\nSince the tavily_search native tool isn't available in my tools list, and I can't run the script via process, let me check if there's another way. \n\nActually, wait - looking at my available tools again:\n- read\n- edit  \n- write\n- process\n- web_fetch\n- image\n\nThe tavily_search tool is NOT listed. This means either:\n1. The plugin isn't installed\n2. The plugin is installed but not configured properly\n3. The plugin requires an API key that isn't set\n\nAccording to the SKILL.md, the plugin requires TAVILY_API_KEY environment variable.\n\nLet me check if there's an extensions directory and what's in it.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a0d20eb6559d4f7e966ace83","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\28964\\.openclaw\\extensions"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":