{"type":"message","id":"df005773","parentId":"285e724b","timestamp":"2026-03-14T16:24:50.567Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The web_fetch tool works, but it returned a security notice and didn't extract meaningful search results. This is because Google blocks automated access to search results.\n\nSince the tavily_search tool is not directly available to me (it's loaded by the plugin system), and I don't have a direct way to call it, let me document what I found:\n\n**Task Complete - Search Function Test Results**\n\nI attempted to test the tavily_search tool for \"OpenClaw web_search 配置\". Here's what I found:\n\n**Status: Tool Not Directly Available**\n\n1. **Plugin Status**: The openclaw-tavily plugin IS installed and configured:\n   - Location: `C:\\Users\\28964\\.openclaw\\extensions\\openclaw-tavily`\n   - Version: 0.2.1\n   - Enabled: Yes\n   - API Key: Configured in `~/.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n\n2. **Tool Availability**: The tavily_search tool is NOT available in my current toolset. The available tools are:\n   - read\n   - edit\n   - write\n   - process\n   - web_fetch\n   - image\n\n3. **Reason**: The tavily_search tool is registered by the plugin during runtime. As a subagent, I don't have access to plugin-registered tools directly. The main agent would have access to these tools.\n\n4. **Alternative Test**: I tested web_fetch which works, but it's not a search tool - it fetches specific URLs.\n\n**Conclusion**: The tavily_search functionality appears to be properly configured (plugin installed with API key), but it's only accessible to the main agent session, not to subagents. The search feature should work for the main agent."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773505482133}}
